00:54:27,935 --> 00:54:31,427
[SPEAKER_10]: Yeah, Ron, do you want to say something?

665
00:54:32,680 --> 00:54:41,726
[SPEAKER_05]: Yeah, I just feel like we're overthinking this process because it's a two thirds of a vote.

666
00:54:42,407 --> 00:54:52,353
[SPEAKER_05]: It's a, you know, any commission that we're talking about, nothing can, you know, you don't look at us and it's taken us 13 months to get to where we are at.

667
00:54:52,413 --> 00:54:56,516
[SPEAKER_05]: So I don't think 30 days is that long to wait for something to happen.

668
00:54:56,536 --> 00:54:57,477
[SPEAKER_05]: I just think that we've,

669
00:54:58,057 --> 00:55:06,500
[SPEAKER_05]: kind of buried this one, and I'm gonna, I'm just, you know, my New Year's resolution is to start putting these things on paper and moving them.

670
00:55:06,960 --> 00:55:12,262
[SPEAKER_05]: So I'm gonna, after Jean says what you want, I'm gonna move the question.

671
00:55:12,982 --> 00:55:14,123
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay, thank you, Ron.

672
00:55:14,503 --> 00:55:14,803
[SPEAKER_10]: Jean?

673
00:55:16,784 --> 00:55:25,947
[SPEAKER_03]: I was looking at last month's materials and Somerville's draft language, and Somerville had

674
00:55:28,138 --> 00:55:44,212
