01:16:53,222 --> 01:16:54,462
[SPEAKER_12]: No, that's Phyllis.

988
01:16:54,662 --> 01:16:55,143
[SPEAKER_10]: Oh, sorry.

989
01:16:59,912 --> 01:17:03,793
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay, so Anthony, sorry, I just gotta write this down.

990
01:17:05,073 --> 01:17:06,713
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay, let's vote.

991
01:17:10,234 --> 01:17:10,634
[SPEAKER_10]: Anthony.

992
01:17:10,654 --> 01:17:12,475
[SPEAKER_11]: Yes.

993
01:17:13,255 --> 01:17:13,695
[SPEAKER_10]: Phyllis.

994
01:17:14,135 --> 01:17:14,415
[SPEAKER_11]: Yes.

995
01:17:15,615 --> 01:17:16,095
[SPEAKER_10]: Paulette.

996
01:17:16,475 --> 01:17:16,735
[SPEAKER_11]: Yes.

997
01:17:17,696 --> 01:17:18,116
[SPEAKER_10]: Aubrey.

998
01:17:20,556 --> 01:17:20,836
[SPEAKER_10]: Yes.

999
01:17:23,677 --> 01:17:23,977
[SPEAKER_10]: Ron.

1000
01:17:26,038 --> 01:17:31,141
[SPEAKER_05]: I'm going to support it with a yes, but I just caution everybody that this is not the procedural way to get this done.

1001
01:17:31,181 --> 01:17:39,405
[SPEAKER_05]: So in the future, when we're doing, you know, finalizing votes, we got to really make sure we're going backwards is not really the way to do it.

1002
01:17:39,445 --> 01:17:40,245
[SPEAKER_05]: But I support this.

1003
01:17:40,905 --> 01:17:42,286
[SPEAKER_05]: I understand what everybody's trying to do.

1004
01:17:42,986 --> 01:17:44,147
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay.

1005
01:17:44,527 --> 01:17:44,947
[SPEAKER_10]: Maury?

1006
01:17:45,888 --> 01:17:46,128
[SPEAKER_05]: Yes.

1007
01:17:46,968 --> 01:17:47,329
[SPEAKER_10]: Eunice?

1008
01:17:50,990 --> 01:17:51,311
[SPEAKER_10]: Yes.

1009
01:17:53,772 --> 01:17:54,132
[SPEAKER_10]: Gene?

1010
01:17:55,070 --> 01:17:55,330
[SPEAKER_10]: Yes.

1011
01:17:56,430 --> 01:17:58,551
[SPEAKER_10]: And I'll vote yes, sure.

1012
01:17:59,871 --> 01:18:07,794
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay, so we have provisional language and we have made a decision.

1013
01:18:07,814 --> 01:18:13,615
[SPEAKER_10]: And great, thank you everyone.

1014
