[SPEAKER_07]: Yeah, congratulations makes sense.

1015
01:18:16,736 --> 01:18:18,877
[SPEAKER_10]: Right.

1016
01:18:19,337 --> 01:18:21,318
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay, so I hope that we could,

1017
01:18:23,833 --> 01:18:26,476
[SPEAKER_10]: I don't think we have, I don't know, I don't know if we have time to.

1018
01:18:27,137 --> 01:18:31,623
[SPEAKER_10]: Is there was there was the other piece that we were maybe going to look at was.

1019
01:18:36,155 --> 01:18:37,676
[SPEAKER_10]: Where did it go?

1020
01:18:37,776 --> 01:18:39,918
[SPEAKER_10]: We have 35 minutes left, Melville.

1021
01:18:39,958 --> 01:18:40,739
[SPEAKER_07]: Yeah, I know.

1022
01:18:40,859 --> 01:18:48,845
[SPEAKER_10]: That's why I'm not sure we should start in on the... Well, let's just take 10 or 15 minutes to... It's not 10 or 15 minutes.

1023
01:18:49,165 --> 01:18:49,465
[SPEAKER_10]: I know.

1024
01:18:49,645 --> 01:18:53,869
[SPEAKER_10]: So, but we're going to take... I'm not saying we'll finish this discussion, but we can start it.

1025
01:18:55,730 --> 01:18:56,631
[SPEAKER_10]: So, we voted.

1026
01:18:59,073 --> 01:19:01,014
[SPEAKER_10]: We did provisional vote on...

1027
01:19:02,776 --> 01:19:07,179
[SPEAKER_10]: hybrid ward representation, but what we didn't decide was the number.

1028
01:19:07,739 --> 01:19:16,505
[SPEAKER_10]: So the subcommittee talked about it and thought 11, eight, and three basically was a good number.

1029
01:19:17,265 --> 01:19:19,827
[SPEAKER_10]: And the other piece that we didn't talk about was term lengths.

1030
01:19:20,487 --> 01:19:24,810
[SPEAKER_10]: So we can start by talking about the number of city councilors.

1031
01:19:26,117 --> 01:19:30,000
[SPEAKER_03]: I don't know that the committee voted on the number.

1032
01:19:30,140 --> 01:19:30,561
[SPEAKER_03]: We didn't.

1033
01:19:30,661 --> 01:19:31,382
[SPEAKER_03]: That's what I'm saying.

1034
01:19:31,422 --> 01:19:34,104
[SPEAKER_03]: We, I was, the subcommittee talked about it.

1035
01:19:34,164 --> 01:19:35,445
[SPEAKER_03]: Oh, I mean the subcommittee.

1036
01:19:35,505 --> 01:19:37,727
[SPEAKER_03]: I don't, I was on that subcommittee.

1037
01:19:37,767 --> 01:19:41,590
[SPEAKER_10]: Oh, no, not the board representation, but the articles two and three, sorry.

1038
01:19:42,371 --> 01:19:42,791
[SPEAKER_10]: Oh, okay.

1039
01:19:43,372 --> 01:19:47,595
[SPEAKER_10]: Because, because the composite, because it's all in article two.

1040
01:19:47,615 --> 01:19:48,416
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay.

1041
01:19:52,644 --> 01:20:01,429
[SPEAKER_10]: I just thought that we could maybe finalize the number that we wanted to include in our draft charter.

1042
01:20:03,430 --> 01:20:03,990
[SPEAKER_10]: Any thoughts?

1043
01:20:06,611 --> 01:20:06,891
[SPEAKER_10]: Eunice.

1044
01:20:07,912 --> 01:20:08,292
[SPEAKER_07]: Yeah.

1045
01:20:08,732 --> 01:20:16,536
[SPEAKER_07]: I mean, we have eight wards, so that would be eight councilors right off the bat with board representation.

1046
01:20:16,556 --> 01:20:20,878
[SPEAKER_07]: Then adding three at large gives us 11.

1047
01:20:22,612 --> 01:20:23,913
[SPEAKER_07]: which I'm fine with.

1048
01:20:24,193 --> 01:20:32,198
[SPEAKER_07]: My concern comes with when we start adding wards, which I think we're really close to doing.

1049
01:20:32,218 --> 01:20:35,980
[SPEAKER_07]: Our population's only growing.

1050
01:20:36,000 --> 01:20:38,881
[SPEAKER_07]: We're at 60,000.

1051
01:20:38,922 --> 01:20:41,663
[SPEAKER_07]: We're only getting bigger.

1052
01:20:42,404 --> 01:20:48,527
[SPEAKER_07]: So if we add another ward, which is kind of what the former election commissioner wanted to do,

1053
01:20:50,685 --> 01:20:59,731
[SPEAKER_07]: but another city council may vote for it, then we have nine city councilors and only two at large.

1054
01:20:59,751 --> 01:21:06,615
[SPEAKER_07]: I don't feel like two at large for a city of 60,000 plus.

1055
01:21:07,596 --> 01:21:11,578
[SPEAKER_07]: If we get to nine wards, we're going to be well over 60,000 people.

1056
01:21:12,119 --> 01:21:14,660
[SPEAKER_07]: I don't feel like two at large is enough.

1057
01:21:16,562 --> 01:21:16,862
[SPEAKER_10]: Yeah.

1058
01:21:17,042 --> 01:21:18,183
[SPEAKER_10]: The wards question is,

1059
01:21:21,876 --> 01:21:26,718
[SPEAKER_10]: I feel like we need to maybe talk to the Collins Center about this again.

1060
01:21:27,238 --> 01:21:41,424
[SPEAKER_10]: When I raised this with them, I believe that the city could add another ward or the state draws the wards and the state can just change the boundary.

1061
01:21:41,624 --> 01:21:46,626
[SPEAKER_10]: I mean, we don't know and we don't really have control over that.

1062
01:21:48,504 --> 01:21:54,529
[SPEAKER_10]: I don't, you know, I don't think we can base our decision on it because we just don't have control over that.

1063
01:21:57,452 --> 01:22:10,804
[SPEAKER_10]: I mean, the subcommittee put in extra language about that there would be either two or three counselors at large, even if the wards changed.

1064
01:22:12,491 --> 01:22:14,172
[SPEAKER_10]: But we can talk about that too.

1065
01:22:14,192 --> 01:22:16,254
[SPEAKER_10]: I don't even know if that language, I don't know.

1066
01:22:16,434 --> 01:22:23,659
[SPEAKER_10]: I mean, again, the call-in center, when they look at that language might, they will often say things that we didn't think of.

1067
01:22:23,979 --> 01:22:31,425
[SPEAKER_10]: So, but thinking, but deciding on the number, right, is something that we do need to do.

1068
01:22:31,985 --> 01:22:32,966
[SPEAKER_10]: So, Dean.

1069
01:22:35,367 --> 01:22:38,670
[SPEAKER_03]: I, well, I was in the ward subcommittee and was,

1070
01:22:40,606 --> 01:22:50,592
[SPEAKER_03]: thinking of more at large, which I realized has a financial consideration that made people nervous.

1071
01:22:53,013 --> 01:23:06,581
[SPEAKER_03]: It just balances out the more local-focused, neighborhood-focused part of the city council with some city councilors who are more focused on at large.

1072
01:23:09,232 --> 01:23:11,497
[SPEAKER_03]: But I don't know how we deal with the financial.

1073
01:23:12,762 --> 01:23:15,464
[SPEAKER_03]: implications of our decision and whether we should.

1074
01:23:15,484 --> 01:23:26,633
[SPEAKER_03]: The other point I just want to say to what Eunice was raising is hopefully we'll be reviewing our charter every 10 years, which I think is standard.

1075
01:23:27,394 --> 01:23:31,057
[SPEAKER_03]: And every 10 years is when the census happens and the rewriting of the ward.

1076
01:23:31,137 --> 01:23:38,622
[SPEAKER_03]: So the charter review committee could look at that and rewrite that.

1077
01:23:39,858 --> 01:23:41,119
[SPEAKER_03]: make up.

1078
01:23:42,040 --> 01:23:56,250
[SPEAKER_03]: But yeah, that's my one concern is just what are the unintended consequences of going from an all at large to a predominantly ward city council and do we want to add a few more at large just to

1079
01:23:59,303 --> 01:24:00,524
[SPEAKER_03]: weigh it out more.

1080
01:24:01,664 --> 01:24:13,049
[SPEAKER_03]: So I see a lot of heads shaking, but that's a concern I have is that it will become more focused on neighborhood issues and won't be thinking of the city as a whole always.

1081
01:24:13,728 --> 01:24:14,749
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay, thank you.

1082
01:24:14,769 --> 01:24:17,773
[SPEAKER_10]: Ron and I think Paulette also.

1083
01:24:17,793 --> 01:24:20,016
[SPEAKER_05]: Go ahead, Ron.

1084
01:24:20,176 --> 01:24:22,419
[SPEAKER_05]: I hear what Jean and Eunice are saying.

1085
01:24:22,439 --> 01:24:31,430
[SPEAKER_05]: I agree with Jean that this is a living document that will have provisions in it to change as we change as a city, but we have to react to

1086
01:24:32,331 --> 01:24:38,880
[SPEAKER_05]: what is here now in terms of adding more at large and watering down what the ward representation is.

1087
01:24:38,940 --> 01:24:44,989
[SPEAKER_05]: We might as well stick with seven at large as opposed to ward representation.

1088
01:24:45,009 --> 01:24:47,051
[SPEAKER_05]: We can go back to that, but I think that

1089
01:24:48,392 --> 01:24:52,755
[SPEAKER_05]: I think 11 is the right number for this right time.

1090
01:24:53,315 --> 01:24:58,057
[SPEAKER_05]: And as Gina's mentioned, the document is certainly amendable and changeable.

1091
01:24:58,157 --> 01:25:10,283
[SPEAKER_05]: So I think, again, my New Year's resolution is gonna come up all year, but I'd like to move the question of 11 city councilors, eight ward representatives, three at large.

1092
01:25:10,988 --> 01:25:13,410
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay, so that's a motion.

1093
01:25:14,130 --> 01:25:16,152
[SPEAKER_10]: Paulette, did you have your hand up just before we?

1094
01:25:17,273 --> 01:25:19,775
[SPEAKER_02]: As it is, we'd be growing from seven to 11.

1095
01:25:20,756 --> 01:25:34,967
[SPEAKER_02]: To me, that certainly is, you know, I've got concerns about it being so big, but so I'm comfortable with saying the 11, but I'm not comfortable with voting for more than that.

1096
01:25:36,408 --> 01:25:36,668
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay.

1097
01:25:37,536 --> 01:25:38,758
[SPEAKER_10]: So Ron made a motion.

1098
01:25:38,778 --> 01:25:40,500
[SPEAKER_10]: Does anybody like this?

1099
01:25:40,960 --> 01:25:44,425
[SPEAKER_06]: I'd like to know if I can add to discussion.

1100
01:25:44,445 --> 01:25:49,351
[SPEAKER_06]: I I'm I'm worried about the number 11.

1101
01:25:49,471 --> 01:25:52,895
[SPEAKER_06]: You know, in my head, I have the number nine.

1102
01:25:55,207 --> 01:26:10,521
[SPEAKER_06]: And I know it doesn't work for folks, but that's what I feel going from seven to nine would be easy for the city and for the city council and how to make that work.

1103
01:26:10,922 --> 01:26:17,168
[SPEAKER_06]: I know the comments that I said, it's a little bit tricky, but a lot of cities have,

1104
01:26:17,965 --> 01:26:23,807
[SPEAKER_06]: Instead of having ward representation, they have district representation where wards are combined.

1105
01:26:24,307 --> 01:26:29,089
[SPEAKER_06]: And I know it's more work, but we've never really looked.

1106
01:26:30,549 --> 01:26:32,850
[SPEAKER_10]: I think there might be one city that does that.

1107
01:26:32,890 --> 01:26:34,250
[SPEAKER_10]: I don't think a lot of cities do it.

1108
01:26:35,331 --> 01:26:36,171
[SPEAKER_06]: Well, Boston does.

1109
01:26:39,397 --> 01:26:41,538
[SPEAKER_06]: Folks always want to be like Boston.

1110
01:26:41,578 --> 01:26:51,381
[SPEAKER_06]: So I'm just saying that, you know, it could, there is, there is, that is an option of having, you know, five at large and four district counselors.

1111
01:26:51,841 --> 01:26:53,462
[SPEAKER_06]: And we've never talked about it.

1112
01:26:53,582 --> 01:27:03,325
[SPEAKER_06]: And, and I know it's more difficult, but it's something that, you know, I think people should at least, you know, kick around in their head a little bit.

1113
01:27:04,817 --> 01:27:14,463
[SPEAKER_10]: Um, we did, we did talk about it a little bit and what we, um, you know, there were, there's potential legal issues with combining wards.

1114
01:27:15,124 --> 01:27:17,665
[SPEAKER_10]: There were, there were some reasons why we didn't pursue it.

1115
01:27:19,286 --> 01:27:27,011
[SPEAKER_10]: Um, so, but, um, I just want to go back because I know Ron made a motion.

1116
01:27:29,092 --> 01:27:30,293
[SPEAKER_08]: I'm going to second that motion.

1117
01:27:31,014 --> 01:27:31,314
[SPEAKER_10]: All right.

1118
01:27:32,715 --> 01:27:41,763
[SPEAKER_10]: All right, so the motion is to have 11 city councilors, eight ward representatives, three at large.

1119
01:27:43,845 --> 01:27:45,607
[SPEAKER_10]: Eunice?

1120
01:27:45,647 --> 01:27:45,887
[SPEAKER_10]: Yes.

1121
01:27:47,288 --> 01:27:47,729
[SPEAKER_10]: Maury?

1122
01:27:49,931 --> 01:27:50,211
[SPEAKER_08]: Yes.

1123
01:27:50,691 --> 01:27:51,132
[SPEAKER_10]: Phyllis?

1124
01:27:57,518 --> 01:27:57,818
[SPEAKER_10]: Phyllis?

1125
01:27:59,370 --> 01:28:00,631
[SPEAKER_10]: Oh, sorry, you're on mute.

1126
