01:28:15,241 --> 01:28:15,662
[SPEAKER_03]: Paulette?

1137
01:28:16,182 --> 01:28:16,462
[SPEAKER_03]: Yes.

1138
01:28:17,323 --> 01:28:17,703
[SPEAKER_03]: Ron?

1139
01:28:18,664 --> 01:28:18,964
[SPEAKER_05]: Yes.

1140
01:28:19,705 --> 01:28:20,185
[SPEAKER_10]: Anthony?

1141
01:28:23,067 --> 01:28:28,651
[SPEAKER_06]: I'll vote yes for solidarity, but I'm more in favor of nine.

1142
01:28:29,590 --> 01:28:30,611
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay, thank you.

1143
01:28:30,871 --> 01:28:32,792
[SPEAKER_10]: So the motion carries.

1144
01:28:33,572 --> 01:28:34,933
[SPEAKER_10]: Wow, that's great.

1145
01:28:35,093 --> 01:28:37,894
[SPEAKER_10]: That's another piece of business that we took care of.

1146
01:28:39,295 --> 01:28:40,915
[SPEAKER_10]: We do have some other things on the agenda.

1147
01:28:40,935 --> 01:28:46,458
[SPEAKER_10]: The only other piece of that section was the term links.

1148
01:28:48,959 --> 01:28:52,861
[SPEAKER_10]: I don't know, we can spend five minutes maybe talking about term links.

1149
01:28:52,921 --> 01:28:54,782
[SPEAKER_10]: I don't know if we'll vote on that tonight, but.

1150
01:28:55,912 --> 01:28:57,752
[SPEAKER_03]: Yeah, I wasn't comfortable with that.

1151
01:28:58,673 --> 01:28:59,913
[SPEAKER_03]: With the two years?

1152
01:29:00,593 --> 01:29:03,654
[SPEAKER_03]: No, just with voting on it today without discussion.

1153
01:29:03,674 --> 01:29:06,954
[SPEAKER_03]: And I wanted to have like more discussion on it.

1154
01:29:07,494 --> 01:29:08,374
[SPEAKER_10]: Yeah.

1155
01:29:08,614 --> 01:29:08,995
[SPEAKER_10]: Yeah.

1156
01:29:09,015 --> 01:29:19,337
[SPEAKER_10]: So we can start and have a brief discussion on the term lengths just to sort of see where people are at or if there's some ideas that people want to throw out for other committee members to think about.

1157
